                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Axen,<br /><br />I started doing Drudges at 56. It seemed pretty easy and I would always grab a virtue from Nexus omw to ME so i hardly ever died. The exp is pretty good but there seems to be alot of down time also. <br /><br />My biggest problem was getting a resist then having to waite 5 mins or /q out after I FD for the mob to reset. <br /><br />as far as mob control. I Trall then /guard haste pet and pull another drudge with a ring i bought that is a 5hp life tap ( usuable from inv. 20pp ) when pet gets on it. slow the bad guy and sit back. A hasted Drudge tears through mobs. Ive had a hasted drdge tank 3 other drudges and 2 bats at 1 time. <br /><br />my spell line up was..<br /><br />( after i am fully buffed , also use manaskin. its usually enough to give u an extra second to get off a FD if u need )<br /><br />1. doomin<br />2. ST.<br />3. Thrall<br />4. Vexing <br />5. Root.<br />with the rest being whatever... o.. FD being 1 more.<br /><br />usually if i pull and get a resist I just FD right away and waite for it to reset or just /q out. 99.00 of the time I play in the hills behind the 3 vamp camps and i pull my pets from the bone piles behind the middle vamp camp. <br /><br />exp from 56-58.5 is about 1% per drudge and .25-.50 per bat.  and .50% from the vamps.<br /><br />my gear is pretty average i think. my necro is an alt so all my DKP goes into my main. <br /><br />buffed w/ virtue and self buffs my HP are about 3300. <br /><br />Good luck. hope that info helped.<br /><br />Dreken <br />58.999 Necro Mith Marr<br />Gobner<br />OverLord Mith Marr<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
