                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I agree with Wurtin. When I dang 54 I went to try Thrall of Bones in The Grey. <br />Around the tempe there are a couple of shissar camps (I would reccomend clearing out golems once with good old Boner). Then, if you are facing the temple entrance, you will see three shissar to your right. Start from those... charm one, shackle the other two (you can throw a ST in on the add but it should not be necessary.. your pet should eat both mobs, shackled. At that point, FD and kill your pet, which should already be low on hps. There are other shissar camps around the temple, I doubt you will be able to single pull anything, but with shackle and ST you should be able to handle adds. If things go wrong, zone into the temple (I reccomed having Harmshield up). <br />Undead skellies (tormented iksar and similar) in the Grey are even better exp, but charm seems to break faster.<br /><br />Zerp<br />SZ</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
